class Solution:
    def minElement(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:
        def digit_sum(x: int) -> int:
            s = 0
            while x > 0:
                s += x % 10
                x //= 10
            return s
        
        return min(digit_sum(x) for x in nums)

"""
Approach & Reasoning:
For each integer x in nums compute its digit sum by repeatedly taking x % 10 and integer-dividing x by 10 until x becomes zero. Track the minimum of these digit sums while iterating over the array once.

Because the problem only asks for the minimum after replacement (not the modified array itself) we never store the intermediate sums; we only keep the running minimum value.

The loop is guaranteed to terminate because every positive integer loses at least one digit per iteration. With n <= 100 and each number having at most 5 digits the total work is negligible.

Time Complexity: O(n * d) where d <= 5 is the maximum number of digits in any element
Space Complexity: O(1)
"""
